The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	The Cricket South Africas security officer Saijul Nagel on Friday inspected Eden Gardens  the venue for the second Test match between India and South Africa from February 14-18. He also inspected the security arrangements at the team hotel and is apparently satisfied with the security plans after speaking to senior police officials.          
	Former South African cricket boards supremo and captain Ali Bacher will be signing the certificates that will be handed over to the blood donors on the Sir Frank Worrell Day celebrated every year by the CAB on February 3.           
	 The CAB tournament committee on Friday dismissed Aryan Clubs charge that two umpires Indranil Chakraborty and Biplab Basu deliberately delayed the start of second days play during their league match against Kumartuli at the Bhowanipore ground. The match ended in a draw. East Bengal opener Partha Sarathi Bhattacharya who was summoned for misbehaviour during a league match tendered an unconditional apology.                
	Cricket: CAB league matches at various grounds from 10 am      
